SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 851
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Cecilio Rodriguez of
Gatlinburg-Pittman High School upon being
named All-County in football.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize and
commend those successful high school athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Cecilio Rodriguez of Gatlinburg-Pittman
High School in Sevier County, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has
proven himself a formidable competitor on the football field; and
WHEREAS, Cecilio Rodriguez was recently named to the All-County team in recognition
of his excellence on the gridiron for Gatlinburg-Pittman High School; and
WHEREAS, a senior two-way player, Mr. Rodriguez was also named to the Tennessee
Sports Writers Association All-State and Tennessee Football Coaches Association All-State
teams; and
WHEREAS, Cecilio Rodriguez recorded 115 rushes for 863 yards and 16 touchdowns
and had 17 receptions for 223 yards and two touchdowns during the 2025 season; and
WHEREAS, a placekicker on special teams, Mr. Rodriguez was successful on 66 of his
71 point-after-touchdown attempts (93%) and was a perfect 6-6 on field goal attempts; and
WHEREAS, Cecilio Rodriguez epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as
he has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off
the field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Rodriguez's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his
family, his community, and his school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this accomplished
athlete; now, therefore,
SJR0851
013252
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Cecilio Rodriguez of
Gatlinburg-Pittman High School on being named to the All-County football team, wishing him
much success and happiness in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
